description: System-generated unique identifier for this alternate part number record.
Date/time the record was last updated, millisecond precision (YYYYMMDDhhmmssSSS); confirm if it represents create vs. update time with SME.
External alternate part number from a manufacturer or supplier that cross-references the internal part.
Free-text notes about the alternate number, such as brand, compatibility, or usage details.
Identifier of the internal part or inventory item to which this alternate number applies.
Code/name of the referenced entity for the part identifier (likely the target table name, e.g., part inventory); confirm with SME.
Identifier of the corresponding record in the legacy system for migration lineage and cross-reference.
Name of the source table in the legacy system associated with the legacy key.
